reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Small and hard to put together
reviews.reviewText: This shelf is so much smaller than I expected but that’s my fault. The directions are awful and one of the holes wasn’t drilled. It will work for now but I would definitely not buy it again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 1, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy Shelf Despite Manufacturing Defect
reviews.reviewText: The shelf is an attractive dark wood color, and is very sturdy. There was a manufacturing defect with mine, such that one of the holes which joins the top and bottom half of the metal frame (and should contain a screw that holds one corner of the middle shelf in place) was misaligned. In the close up photo you can see that the pass through hole is misaligned. The structural integrity of the shelf still seems okay however, as the other attachment points for this middle shelf are strong. This was easy to put together, however the finish on the wood is VERY shiny, and seems to easily pick up smudges from natural skin oils from normal handling.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 29, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice not-too-tall shelf
reviews.reviewText: I needed a shelf that was not too tall and this fit the bill. I bought it to put some books on. I like how it's enclosed so you can lean books on it. Some shelfs are more open and the books are more likely to fall.There is an ever-so-slight wobble, but the more books you put on it, the more it goes away.
